node.text: Had so much fun with @jennifer.garner @edgarramirez25 @julianlerner and @everlyeverwhere, can’t wait for you all to watch the film on @netflix March 12. Join the fun and have a Yes Day of your own! I wanna see your Yes Day activities so share how you’re celebrating using #YESDAYChallenge on March 12. @netflixfamily

node.text: June is National Acne Awareness Month so I wanted to share two products that I consistently use within my routine to keep my skin clear. I have been using the @neutrogena Oil-Free Acne Wash Pink Grapefruit collection for years! This facial cleanser removes oil and dirt that can clog pores with 2% Salicylic Acid, yet rinses clean without over-drying. The Body Clear Body Wash Pink Grapefruit is perfect to clear and help prevent any body acne. Bonus: they both smell amazing! #NTGspokesperson

node.text:
If there’s one thing I've learned recently, it’s the massive buying power one community holds within their hands. 63% of Asian, Black, and Hispanic American adults believe that skincare brands are less likely to design products for the needs of people with Black and Brown skin ultimately leaving an entire community feeling discouraged and neglected. That’s why I am so excited to partner with my Neutrogena family on For People with Skin - a long-term commitment to advance skin health for all consumers regardless of race, age, ethnicity, skin need, or income.
 
Through this game-changing program, Neutrogena is using an inclusive approach to identify key insights that drive meaningful product innovations and relevant claims in products that are safe for all consumers across the full Fitzpatrick scale of skin tones. Check out Neutrogena The Bar for more information. #ForPeopleWithSkin #NTGSpokesperson

node.text: The Fallout won the Grand Jury Prize for best film and our incredible director @meganparkithere won the Brightcove Award for best director on the rise!! So thrilled. Thank you a million times over to Megan for trusting me with Vada and this story and to everyone who was any help in getting this film made. Special thanks to @sxsw and @franciaraisa, my sweet friend who suggested me for the role and is the reason I got to be apart of this in the first place.

Photo by Jenna Ortega on March 19, 2021. May be an image of one or more people, body of water and text that says 'SXSW Film Festival: Emotionally- Charged Drama 'The Fallout' And Docu 'Lily Topples the World' Among Jury Award Winners By Dino-Ray Ramos March 19, 2021 9:00am f'.

Photo by Jenna Ortega on March 19, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Feature Film Grand Jury Awards TIP US DEADLINE NARRATIVE FEATURE COMPETITION Winner: The Fallout Director: Megan Park "The Fallout takes us through the emotionally charged healing journey of a young girl whose life is forever changed in the wake of a school tragedy. Writer and director Megan Park delivers a timely, riveting, and thought thought-provoking film on the toll it takes on a teenager who is facing a world where they no longer feel safe. It is an intense, moving piece that highlights an important issue to which one can't help but feel connected."'.

Photo by Jenna Ortega on March 19, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'SXSW Special Awards Brightcove Illumination Award The Brightcove Illumination Award honors a filmmaker on the rise, celebrating the innovation and creativity of new artists within the SXSW Film Festival official selections. Brightcove Illumination Award Presented to: The Fallout Director: Megan Park "For her empathetic and honest exploration of life after tragedy, inspired craft, and stellar guidance of a talented young cast, we award the Brightcove Illumination Award to Megan Park for her The Fallout."'.
